snippet: Four rockets were launched from the coastal city of Wonsan, flying 96 miles before crashing into the sea between the Korean Peninsula and Japan, a South Korean Defense Ministry spokesman said.
abstract: North Korea tests new multiple-rocket launcher with range long enough to strike major American and South Korean military bases south of Seoul; tests are seen as latest show of force as United States and South Korea conduct annual joint military exercises.
lead_paragraph: Four rockets were launched from the coastal city of Wonsan, flying 96 miles before crashing into the sea between the Korean Peninsula and Japan, a South Korean Defense Ministry spokesman said.

headline.main: North Korea Tests Rocket Launcher With Range Beyond Seoul, South Says
headline.print_headline: North Korea Tests Launcher With Range Beyond Seoul, South Says
